---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  role="Software Engineer | SDLC & AI Strategy Architect"
  description="CV for Germán Aliprandi focused on AI workflow design, SDLC modernization, and agentic architecture leadership."
  url="https://galiprandi.github.io/me/em"
  title="Germán Aliprandi"
  multiPage={true}
>
  <main>
    <section class="section profile">
      <h3 class="upper">Summary (Profile)</h3>
      <p class="light small-in-print">
        Software Engineer with over 20 years of technical expertise,
        specializing in transforming the Software Development Lifecycle (SDLC)
        through innovative architectures and large-scale AI adoption. Creator of <strong
          >Axioma</strong
        >, a clean-architecture framework designed to lead the next decade of
        AI-assisted development by decoupling business logic for seamless
        agentic orchestration. Currently focused on industrializing engineering
        processes and designing "Agent-First" workflows for high-scale
        organizations.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section profile">
      <h3 class="upper">Strategic Flagship: Axioma</h3>
      <p class="light small-in-print">
        An infrastructure-agnostic framework designed for the AI era. It
        eliminates friction between LLMs and complex systems via a
        contract-based structure, allowing AI agents to understand and execute
        business logic autonomously. Currently serving as the architectural
        engine for Cencosud’s SDLC transformation, enabling contract-based AI
        orchestration.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section profile">
      <h3 class="upper">Professional Experience</h3>
      <ul>
        <li class="light small-in-print">
          <strong
            >Cencosud S.A. — Software Engineer (Dec 2025 – Present):</strong
          > Leading a radical shift in the software construction model for +800 developers
          and 120,000 employees, redefining the technology strategy through AI.
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>SDLC Re-engineering (Global Strategy):</strong> Original Agent-First
              workflow, <strong
                >selected over alternatives from Google, AWS, and Microsoft</strong
              > due to its end-to-end SDLC coverage (User Story → PR); projected <strong
                >2x–3x faster TTM</strong
              > and reduced ambiguity.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Agent Infrastructure (MCP):</strong> Standardized agent access
              to tools/data using MCP for coherent, scalable automation.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Release Operational Efficiency:</strong> Rebuilt Android/iOS
              release flow with orchestrated bash scripts; cut manual work from <strong
                >50</strong
              > minutes to <strong>5</strong> automated, eliminating human error.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Quality Engineering & Data Insights:</strong> Living documentation
              auto-maintained; real-time progress for executive decision-making.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="light small-in-print">
          <strong
            >Rooftop — Senior Technical Interviewer / Staff Consultant (Jul 2025
            – Dec 2025):</strong
          > Specialized technical validation and talent calibration for global partners.
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Senior Talent Assessment:</strong> Executed 50+ deep-dive technical
              assessments for Senior Node.js, React, and AI roles, ensuring elite-level
              talent acquisition for global partners.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Technical Benchmarking:</strong> Standardized evaluation metrics
              for system architecture and problem-solving, directly impacting the
              quality of high-performance engineering squads.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Staffing Consultancy:</strong> Advised on aligning technical
              profiles with business needs to support modern, scalable architectures.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <div class="force-break"></div>

    <section class="section profile">
      <h3 class="upper">Professional Experience (Continued)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li class="light small-in-print">
          <strong
            >Egg Live — Engineering Manager / Software Engineer (Jun 2021 –
            Present):</strong
          > Evolved from frontend architecture definition to technical leadership;
          scaled platform to 50x concurrent users.
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>B2B Ecosystem Integration:</strong> Event-driven architecture
              (CloudEvents + RabbitMQ) to connect LMS clients (Mercado Libre, Telefónica,
              Globant).
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>AI Agent Orchestration:</strong> General-purpose API on <strong
                >fastify-lm</strong
              > for rapid agent creation (LLM selection, prompts, tools).
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Culture & Talent Management:</strong> P&amp;CR program; mentored
              30+ developers during hypergrowth.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Frontend Architecture:</strong> Core redesign (TanStack Query
              + WebSockets): 10x fewer API calls, real-time state for 5k+ concurrent
              users.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section profile">
      <ul>
        <li class="light small-in-print">
          <strong>Gadget — Software Engineer (Apr 2010 – Jun 2021):</strong> Led modernization
          from legacy to scalable SaaS.
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Architectural Modernization:</strong> Built core architectures
              with React, Node.js, AWS; migrated legacy workflows to cloud/CDN stacks.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Industry Transformation:</strong> Delivered interactive digital
              galleries, replacing physical media.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Scalability:</strong> Maintained 98.7% uptime; optimized performance
              for niche, high-value platforms.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="light small-in-print">
          <strong
            >LBC Tech (ex Luis Brunelli y Cía) — Founding Lead &amp; Business
            Strategist (Jan 2004 – Mar 2010):</strong
          > Built the technology division from zero and drove national expansion.
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>IT Department Foundation:</strong> Strategy, staffing, and operations;
              built a 13-person team.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Expansion &amp; Supply Chain:</strong> US provider network and
              national logistics; presence across the country.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Transformation Vision:</strong> Converted diversification into
              a large tech/hardware operation with new revenue streams.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section profile">
      <h3 class="upper">Open Source & Ecosystem Impact</h3>
      <ul>
        <li class="light small-in-print">
          <strong>fastify-lm:</strong> Standardizing LLM integration for the Fastify
          ecosystem.
        </li>
        <li class="light small-in-print">
          <strong>mcp-vs-fnc:</strong> Comparative research on AI communication protocols
          to guide agent interoperability.
        </li>
        <li class="light small-in-print">
          <strong>development-guide:</strong> Engineering culture and standards for
          high-performance teams.
        </li>
        <li class="light small-in-print">
          <strong>@interpolator/xlsx:</strong> Dynamic document automation engine
          for business processes.
        </li>
        <li class="light small-in-print">
          <strong>@galiprandi/array-tools:</strong> High-performance JavaScript utilities
          for SQL-like operations on arrays.
        </li>
        <li class="light small-in-print">
          <strong>@galiprandi/react-tools:</strong> Lightweight React utilities and
          components for UI productivity.
        </li>
        <li class="light small-in-print">
          <strong>zero-ui:</strong> Concept exploration of invisible interfaces.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section profile">
      <h3 class="upper">Footer</h3>
      <p class="light small-in-print manifesto">
        "Built for the next decade of AI-driven engineering."
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  body {
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .force-break {
    break-before: page;
  }

  @media screen {
    .section p,
    .section li {
      line-height: 1.55;
    }
  }

  @media print {
    @page {
      size: A4;
      margin: 12mm 14mm;
    }

    .force-break {
      break-before: page;
    }

    body {
      font-size: 10.5pt;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }

    .section {
      margin-bottom: 0.8em;
    }

    ul {
      margin-top: 0.3em;
      gap: 0.4em;
    }
  }

  .manifesto {
    text-align: center;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }
</style>
